Rating: 3
I made this twice with regular whole wheat lasagna and mozzarella and was pleased with the result (I always mix the spinach and cheese fillings together too). Much more flavorful than veggie lasagna often is. Today I made the recipe with fontina and no boil noodles, as written, and I actually think it's better with mozz. Fontina is too soft to stand up to the rather mushy filling. It absorbed some of the liquid from the sauce and became slimy. I think the recipe works better with the chewiness of mozzarella. I also found the no boil noodles to be thin and quite soft as well. The result was more cohesive than with sturdy whole wheat noodles but also less filling and texturally interesting. Kinda like eating a bowl of lasagna pudding. Also, since the noodles aren't boiled in salted water the lasagna was a bit bland overall. I would recommend oversalting the filling a bit to compensate.

