I love lasagna, but it always seems like such a huge production. This one cuts down the prep time considerably. I agree with other reviewers - if you have a favorite homemade marinara, by all means use that. I also made a homemade parsley-mint pesto, and that was just amazing with the spinach. Tons of flavor! I prefer fresh mozzarella to Fontina, so I made that substitution. Also, a little-known trick is that you don't need special no-boil lasagna noodles, nor do you need to pre-cook regular noodles. Just layer the raw noodles with the sauces and cheese as usual, and really and truly, the liquid in the sauces will cook the noodles. Take that leap of faith, and I guarantee you won't be disappointed. :)

